### Auth Service API Tests
### Base URL and Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8081/api/auth
@contentType = application/json

###
### Health Check
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
### Register New User - Success Case
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "email": "testuser1@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

###
### Register New User - Second User
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser2",
  "email": "testuser2@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass456!"
}

###
### Register Duplicate Username - Should Fail
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "email": "different@example.com",
  "password": "AnotherPass789!"
}

###
### Register Duplicate Email - Should Fail
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "differentuser",
  "email": "testuser1@example.com",
  "password": "AnotherPass789!"
}

###
### Login - Valid Credentials
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

###
### Login - Invalid Password - Should Fail
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser1",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

###
### Login - Nonexistent User - Should Fail
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "nonexistentuser",
  "password": "SomePassword123"
}

###
### Refresh Token - Valid Token
### Note: Replace TOKEN with actual refresh token from login response
###

POST {{baseUrl}}/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.placeholder

###
### Get Current User - Requires Valid Access Token
### Note: Replace TOKEN with actual access token from login response
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.placeholder

###
### Get Current User - No Token - Should Fail
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
### Get Current User - Invalid Token - Should Fail
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

###
### Get User by ID - Requires Valid Access Token
### Note: Replace 1 with actual user ID and TOKEN with valid access token
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/user/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.placeholder

###
### Get User by ID - No Token - Should Fail
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/user/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
### Get User by ID - Nonexistent User - Should Fail
### Note: Replace TOKEN with actual valid access token
###

GET {{baseUrl}}/user/99999
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.placeholder

###
### Actuator Health Endpoint
###

GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/health
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
### Actuator Metrics
###

GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/metrics
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###
### Test CORS - Preflight Request
###

OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/register
Origin: http://localhost:3000
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST
Access-Control-Request-Headers: Content-Type

###
